; Doc - Annex 1 - 2.6 - Pre-Processor Directives

; this section refers a lot to annex 2; 4.2.1; so more extensive class tests should go there.
; but a few basic tests here that check if declaration works, from my current understanding:

; test different class name literals
!class (position x:nb y:nb)
!class (fruit kcal:nb)
!class (car speed:nb acceleration:nb handling:nb)

; test different class member declarations (e.g. x:nb)
!class (members1 number:nb timestamp:us boolean:bl)
!class (members2 group_id:sid device_function_id:fid device_id:did)
!class (members3 set:[] string:st)
!class (fruit_salad ingredient1:fruit ingredient2:fruit)
!class (any_type wildcard: )

; test class templates
!class (template :~ :~)
!class (iTemplate {template nil })

; iterative member declaration
!class (iterative list_of_numbers ::nb)

; forward class directive
!class future
!class (past x:future)